1
00:00:02,410 --> 00:00:06,030
My father was an innocent man,
destroyed by powerful people

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:07,620
The Graysons are behind this

3
00:00:07,860 --> 00:00:08,590
They're gonna pay

4
00:00:08,860 --> 00:00:11,420
I've dedicated my life
to avenging his death

5
00:00:11,760 --> 00:00:13,640
Eventually,someone's gonna find you out

6
00:00:14,030 --> 00:00:16,740
And I won't stop until
they've all paid the price

7
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:20,270
You will always be the clueless
frat boy who crashed your car,

8
00:00:20,460 --> 00:00:23,620
crushed my spine,and never looked back

9
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:24,640
She lost her job

10
00:00:24,780 --> 00:00:26,400
Helping her get another
was the least I could do

11
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,340
I thought you were set
for life,Sara.I'm sorry

12
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,740
Why are you doing this,Daniel

13
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:31,990
To earn your forgiveness

14
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:34,700
You're the first person in a long
time to be able to make me smile

15
00:00:35,050 --> 00:00:39,360
Jack went to Conrad and told him
that Patrick tampered with his brakes

16
00:00:39,490 --> 00:00:42,090
He's probably being chased
out of town as we speak

17
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:44,510
Conrad is a ruthless man.You're not safe

18
00:00:44,740 --> 00:00:45,990
- I can't.
- Go.

19
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:53,700
Growing up,my father said
the ocean was a great escape

20
00:00:55,760 --> 00:01:00,470
As time passed,I also learned that
its expanse holds greater secrets

21
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,330
and the ability to hold mine...

22
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:09,510
And that like love,it is at its heart
fluid,powerful,and sometimes violent

23
00:01:10,150 --> 00:01:13,120
Next time you're here, the authorities
will have Victoria in custody

24
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,560
Soon after,I'll take
you away from everything

25
00:01:16,710 --> 00:01:17,700
And everyone

26
00:01:21,620 --> 00:01:24,660
But in its harshest reality,
the ocean is a barrier

27
00:01:25,930 --> 00:01:27,720
separating you from those you love

28
00:01:29,210 --> 00:01:34,000
When this is done,I'll never
see my sister again... Or Nolan

29
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,370
I know

30
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,270
You'll be okay

31
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:50,500
Are you writing a letter to
Patrick-- Your natural born killer

32
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,300
It's the only means of correspondence

33
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:54,810
I have to keep away from the
prying eyes of the minions

34
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,370
I'm sure you have looking for him

35
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,720
Why would I waste the time and effort

36
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:03,350
It's that smug smirk I'm
going to miss the least

37
00:02:03,450 --> 00:02:06,440
after we've converted our money,
and I have left you for good

38
00:02:06,630 --> 00:02:11,310
Now there's an action that may compel me to
hire some folks to go looking for your boy

39
00:02:11,490 --> 00:02:13,310
Excuse my confusion,Conrad,

40
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:17,890
but are you threatening
Patrick to keep me by your side

41
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:20,270
You know,I believe I am...

42
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:24,950
Starting with your magnificent presence
downstairs for the little Grayson confab

43
00:02:25,170 --> 00:02:26,650
you've obviously forgotten about

44
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:28,370
I've enlisted a PR

45
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:32,270
specialist to help right
the course of my trajectory

46
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:35,800
So if you value Patrick's
freedom, you know,

47
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:40,330
you may want to find some public
worth in the family you still have

48
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:45,450
I still don't see why we're here

49
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:48,450
If my father wants to rehab
his image, he can do it himself

50
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:50,890
I've already educated
him on re-branding

51
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:53,590
and how you're all an
extension of his good name

52
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:54,780
I'm a Clarke

53
00:02:54,990 --> 00:02:55,920
Whoever you are

54
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:59,860
That whole "slumming it
in Montauk" thing... Gold

55
00:03:00,090 --> 00:03:02,080
People love it when
the rich help the poor

56
00:03:02,650 --> 00:03:05,310
But where's the bang for my wedding buck

57
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:08,280
There were no cameras
when you went ring shopping

58
00:03:08,550 --> 00:03:10,310
Has the venue even been announced

59
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:12,140
Who's making the cake

60
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,820
We are not a very showy couple

61
00:03:14,390 --> 00:03:17,540
Is it we?Or is it you?

62
00:03:18,140 --> 00:03:23,120
I am damn good at doing my
research, and you're a mystery

63
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,570
You need to be more like Daniel

64
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:29,720
That publisher's profile is exactly
the kind of rebound story I love

65
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:33,880
Hurt a girl... Tortured
soul... Redemption

66
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:36,530
And I just hired Sara at the Stowaway

67
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:39,840
- Really?
- We ran into her. It's a long story

68
00:03:40,260 --> 00:03:41,440
One I need to hear

69
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,490
If I am to guide your father
back into America's hearts,

70
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:47,080
I run the narrative on
this family from here on out

71
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:50,600
I see you couldn't even extend the courtesy of waiting,
- Ms Preston

72
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:52,500
- "Bizzy," please.
- Bizzy

73
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:54,570
It's such a pleasure,Victoria

74
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:58,660
And I figured I might as well get a jump
on the kids so as not to waste your time

75
00:03:58,970 --> 00:04:01,090
While I applaud your gumption,Bizzy,

76
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:03,640
I feel this Independence
Day party I'm throwing,

77
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:05,310
along with Emily's wedding shower,

78
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,740
should prove sufficient
for the society papers

79
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:12,080
That won't help if those rags
think that you two are still at odds

80
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:15,880
The last event you attended led
to a fight worthy of pay-per-view

81
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:20,220
And since there is little
benefit in positioning Conrad

82
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:22,740
as master of a house divided,

83
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:25,390
I need to rewrite your story... Pronto

84
00:04:25,570 --> 00:04:26,900
And how do you propose to do that

85
00:04:27,110 --> 00:04:30,380
First off,I am plugging
your 4th of July party

86
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:33,510
as the reintroduction of
the happy Grayson clan,

87
00:04:33,790 --> 00:04:37,480
followed by a
mother/daughter-in-law goodwill tour

88
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:38,590
that I will lay out for you

89
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:40,050
when the three of us have lunch tomorrow

90
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:47,220
Right there... That's
all I need-- You two

91
00:04:47,790 --> 00:04:48,940
And that's what I'm gonna get

92
00:04:58,010 --> 00:04:59,620
Trying to get some scoop on the wedding

93
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:01,650
They've got big things planned

94
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:03,260
I'm sure they do

95
00:05:04,610 --> 00:05:05,560
What brings you by

96
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:10,340
I... brought you some
macaroons to welcome you back

97
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:14,660
Thanks. That's a nice surprise

98
00:05:15,950 --> 00:05:16,740
How was LA

99
00:05:18,130 --> 00:05:22,560
Wining and dining photographers for Voulez
is not as glamorous as one might think

100
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:24,090
Oh,really?Weird

101
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,240
I've had a totally different
experience when doing it

102
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:33,710
I don't suppose you're free tonight

103
00:05:35,530 --> 00:05:38,510
He comes bearing gifts, and
now he's looking for a date

104
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,340
I should leave town more often

105
00:05:42,340 --> 00:05:42,880
But no

106
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,300
I have too much work to catch up
on with the wedding approaching

107
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:46,960
Ah,it'll still be here tomorrow

108
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:51,290
Don't let the Graysons
take over your life

109
00:05:55,320 --> 00:06:00,470
- Hi.
- I've lost my touch

110
00:06:01,090 --> 00:06:06,560
A week later,and all I've dug up is a
one-way flight from Philly to Richmond

111
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:09,950
I just want to know
that Patrick's all right

112
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:12,190
Well,you should be
happy that he's not here

113
00:06:12,420 --> 00:06:15,400
He would also be scrutinized
by the publicist Conrad hired

114
00:06:15,420 --> 00:06:17,800
She wants me and Victoria
to play nice for the press

115
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,100
Oh,you and
Vicki,besties--

116
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:24,650
That kind of runs counter to your master
plan of framing her for your murder now

117
00:06:24,790 --> 00:06:30,030
Exactly.Which is why PR maven
Bizzy Preston is becoming a problem

118
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,290
that I don't have time for

119
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,240
What,you know her

120
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,650
And loathe her

121
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:43,450
Back in the day,I was,uh,dating this guy

122
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:46,480
It was casual... fun

123
00:06:47,050 --> 00:06:51,380
Then I met his sister--
Up-and-coming pop star,Sage

124
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:58,040
And she was more casual,more
fun... And as it turned out,married

125
00:06:58,490 --> 00:07:03,170
The press got ahold of our one-hit
wonder, and Bizzy squashed it...

126
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:05,630
By claiming I was gay

127
00:07:05,890 --> 00:07:08,670
I remember when that
happened.It was right when we met

128
00:07:09,260 --> 00:07:10,730
I didn't know that she was behind it

129
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:12,740
Neither did my father

130
00:07:15,690 --> 00:07:18,050
After years of being estranged,

131
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:22,970
Nolcorp's success had finally
gotten us back on good terms,

132
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:27,500
even planning a visit to New
York to see my R&D facility

133
00:07:28,530 --> 00:07:30,690
Programmed a robot to open him a beer

134
00:07:30,970 --> 00:07:39,810
Then... He read the press release,
canceled his trip... Never spoke to me again

135
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,580
I'm sorry,Nolan

136
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:48,490
Bizzy's the one who should be sorry

137
00:07:49,990 --> 00:07:53,590
And we have to stop you from becoming
the next victim of her PR machine

138
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:56,600
She makes a living covering
her clients' secrets

139
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:58,140
We just have to expose them

140
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,470
Yeah,but that's not a simple task

141
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:04,360
She would do anything to protect
'em, and the greater the retainer,

142
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,590
the bigger her allegiance

143
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,260
And I know a family
who's paying top dollar

144
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:11,160
What are you thinking

145
00:08:12,220 --> 00:08:14,890
She could help us with Victoria
before we make her suffer

146
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:17,730
It's not that easy

147
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:22,320
She's smart,dangerous,lethal
with information

148
00:08:23,380 --> 00:08:25,000
Well,I'm not afraid to give her some

149
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:29,810
It's time she found out
about my first husband

