153
00:08:55,110 --> 00:08:59,000
Things were slow back there,so,I
whipped up a little something

154
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:02,440
Is this another attempt to
get desserts put on the menu

155
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,210
Can you blame a girl for trying

156
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:06,040
I'm glad you joined the crew around here

157
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,730
You're a-- You're a
breath of fresh air

158
00:09:09,970 --> 00:09:10,710
Thanks

159
00:09:11,140 --> 00:09:12,910
I got some stuff to do in the storeroom

160
00:09:17,790 --> 00:09:19,420
I was just on my way out to lunch

161
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,020
I hope you don't mind me stopping by

162
00:09:21,490 --> 00:09:22,530
Well,it is a bar

163
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:23,770
That's kinda the point,right

164
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:26,340
You settling in

165
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,670
It's only been a
week,but I can't complain

166
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:31,240
You obviously miss
your job at the bakery

167
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,290
I know that look

168
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:37,080
It means you got something on the brain

169
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:40,610
I know this pastry thing has
always been a dream of yours

170
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:43,340
And this might sound crazy,but...

171
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:46,600
What if you were to make
the cake for my wedding

172
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:49,200
Right... 'Cause that wouldn't be weird

173
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:52,260
Only if we make it weird.Come
on.We haven't hired anybody yet

174
00:09:52,590 --> 00:09:56,340
You know... When I saw you
the other night after my shift,

175
00:09:56,490 --> 00:09:58,060
I thought you were just
handing me a bunch of crap

176
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,540
about earning my forgiveness

177
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:01,160
I told you,that's not who I am anymore

178
00:10:01,730 --> 00:10:04,020
- I want to help.
- I don't want your charity,Danny

179
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:05,560
Good,'cause I'm not offering you any

180
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,590
What I am offering is a
chance at a job you want--

181
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:10,420
One that could be good for you

182
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:15,070
Think about it

183
00:10:19,590 --> 00:10:23,160
Like I said,he'd be perfect for
a profile piece in your magazine

184
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,300
Think about it

185
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,100
Sorry

186
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:29,890
This thing beats more
often than my heart

187
00:10:30,210 --> 00:10:33,060
Especially now that I'm keeping
you all dry under my umbrella

188
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:36,700
Conrad did not tell me just how much
this family was weighing him down

189
00:10:37,790 --> 00:10:39,370
I don't understand.Is that why I'm here

190
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:44,240
a blogger called about a piece that
I planted about you and Daniel--

191
00:10:44,570 --> 00:10:47,900
How socialite Emily Thorne
waited to find her Prince Charming

192
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:48,820
It's... good

193
00:10:49,770 --> 00:10:55,940
But... This weasel claims to have
proof that you were hitched before

194
00:10:56,780 --> 00:10:57,490
What

195
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:05,260
I was really young.It was a mistake

196
00:11:05,460 --> 00:11:06,640
I mean,surely you understand

197
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:13,730
Actually... I'm one of the lucky few who
was right about her high school sweetheart

198
00:11:15,090 --> 00:11:17,450
Jeff and I have been
together for 22 years

199
00:11:18,540 --> 00:11:21,290
And we are still as in love
as I'm sure you and Daniel are

200
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:22,190
This can't get out

201
00:11:22,410 --> 00:11:23,170
I'm a gravedigger,babe

202
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:25,010
I bury things bigger than this every day

203
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,380
Good,'cause nobody can
know,especially Victoria

204
00:11:29,410 --> 00:11:30,860
We're not really the best of friends

205
00:11:32,050 --> 00:11:33,250
I just can't win with her

206
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:36,200
If she finds this out,she
will never forgive me

207
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,630
Well... I caught the bullet this time

208
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:42,130
But secrets have a way of bleeding out

209
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:43,710
So let's cut to the chase

210
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,400
What else are you hiding

211
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:47,700
Nothing,I swear

212
00:11:59,290 --> 00:12:00,280
Can I help you with something

213
00:12:02,540 --> 00:12:06,570
Conrad's hired a publicist who's determined
to put a sheen on everything we do,

214
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,550
including promoting this wedding,

215
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:12,080
which if we don't act quickly,
it'll be too late to do anything

216
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:14,380
I thought you were relying on Jack Porter
- to break them up

217
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:16,680
- I've heard that he's
courting Ms Lemarchal

218
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:18,770
So clearly that won't
be coming to fruition

219
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,650
- Then we'll find another way.
- Oh,we won't

220
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:23,960
You will

221
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,130
My son has no shortage
of hatred towards you

222
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:33,670
So get back in Emily's life...
And more importantly,her bed

223
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,850
The blogger persona was convincing

224
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:40,680
Let's just hope Bizzy spreads
the news like I want her to

225
00:12:40,890 --> 00:12:41,810
Oh,trust me

226
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:45,770
She knows that sharing information like
that keeps her on the Grayson payroll

227
00:12:46,180 --> 00:12:51,530
And once she does,the two of
us will Biz-mantle her with glee

228
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,070
You sure you're up for it,Grandpa

229
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:58,650
I'm not getting older,just... wiser

230
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:04,800
But trying to unearth Bizzy's clients'
secrets is taking longer than I thought

231
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:08,450
Hacking her proton 5 firewall
will take time that I don't have

232
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:10,490
Why the look

233
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:13,430
If this had happened a few years ago,

234
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:16,780
you would have thrown a martini
in her face and called it a day

235
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:20,470
But now... I'm standing up for myself

236
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:27,160
I just... Buried the pain of
what happened with my father,

237
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:31,690
but because of you,I'm
not just facing it

238
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:33,280
I'm doing something

239
00:13:35,070 --> 00:13:37,220
I've learned a lot from you,Ems

240
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:39,380
We made a great team

241
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:46,580
Well,if we're gonna win...
We're gonna need a new game plan

242
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:50,580
I don't have the time for this firewall,
so we've got to get her password

243
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:52,580
Except that phone never leaves her hands

244
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,240
Maybe it doesn't need to

245
00:14:12,490 --> 00:14:14,500
I'm glad I decided to
take the evening off

