00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:25,700
Yeah,it's like your own little sanctuary

248
00:14:27,790 --> 00:14:30,250
Where no one can find us

249
00:14:49,230 --> 00:14:51,210
- What.Have I done something wrong?
- No.No

250
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:58,820
It's... Let's just try to enjoy the
movie and have another glass of wine

251
00:15:00,820 --> 00:15:04,290
Unless... I can go downstairs
and make another drink

252
00:15:04,690 --> 00:15:06,600
No,I don't need anything from the bar

253
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:08,410
Wine it is,then

254
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:11,900
That's not what I meant

255
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:20,530
Okay,I think it's best if I go

256
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,640
- Margaux.
- It's okay.I have an early morning

257
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,480
Enjoy your beautiful evening

258
00:15:38,690 --> 00:15:39,340
You're late

259
00:15:40,110 --> 00:15:41,270
Daniel held me up

260
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:44,060
He wants his ex-girlfriend
to make our wedding cake

261
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,910
He set up a tasting at my house tomorrow

262
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:48,320
Do you suspect something's amiss

263
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:51,000
No.I'm sure he's doing it out of guilt

264
00:15:51,330 --> 00:15:53,020
Daniel's the reason I
needed to meet with you

265
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:55,090
Victoria's compelled me
to get back into your orbit

266
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:57,050
in order to drive a wedge
between the two of you

267
00:15:57,660 --> 00:15:59,600
Well,that's not an option,not
this close to the wedding

268
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:02,290
Yeah,but if I don't see it through,
I may lose access to the Graysons

269
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,390
Maybe there's a third way

270
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,120
And that is

271
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:10,270
To be seen together...

272
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:26,930
This is the last one,I promise

273
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,000
Are you kidding me?Each one's
been better than the last

274
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,910
Are these family recipes

275
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:32,580
Yeah,passed down from my mom's side

276
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,210
Well,your mom taught you well

277
00:16:34,470 --> 00:16:37,380
Well,she raised me and my
brother after my dad ditched us,

278
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:41,860
so everything I know I learned from
her,including how to make a mess

279
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:43,890
I am so sorry about this disaster

280
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:45,050
Oh,don't worry about it

281
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:48,720
But... I better stop,or I'll be
full for my lunch with Victoria

282
00:16:49,020 --> 00:16:52,010
Well,if it'd help make the
lunch shorter, I'd say eat up

283
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:55,550
Thanks again... For giving me a shot

284
00:16:55,930 --> 00:16:58,520
Of course.Thank you .See ya

285
00:16:59,410 --> 00:17:02,210
Hey... I really appreciate
you considering this

286
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:04,890
It's just something I...
I want to do,you know

287
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:05,900
It's a great thing that you're doing

288
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:09,840
And I... I think she'll
make a wonderful wedding cake

289
00:17:10,810 --> 00:17:11,350
Me,too

290
00:17:11,990 --> 00:17:12,850
I'll see you later,okay

291
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:17,530
- You got the job.
- Shut up

292
00:17:17,860 --> 00:17:20,030
- Seriously?
- I'm serious

293
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:24,800
Man,she is way more mature than I am

294
00:17:25,050 --> 00:17:28,540
I mean... Letting your fiancé's
ex make your wedding cake--

295
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:29,660
If the tables were turned,

296
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:32,100
I would be so jealous and would
have canceled the whole thing

297
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:33,670
Oh,well,that's Emily

298
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:39,140
And you... Even asking her to let
me make the cake-- That took guts

299
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:40,310
I mean,what if these were awful

300
00:17:40,550 --> 00:17:41,370
I knew they wouldn't be

301
00:17:41,710 --> 00:17:45,060
I gotta say that,uh... Forgiveness
thing you were looking for...

302
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,280
This goes a long way toward it

303
00:17:50,730 --> 00:17:53,780
-  Well...I should clean up.
- Okay

304
00:17:54,190 --> 00:17:55,200
Hey,let me help you .I got it

305
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:57,670
- I can help
- No,Danny,you hired me.It's my job

306
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,570
Then I'm giving you
the rest of the day off

307
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:00,830
Go home

308
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:08,200
So... How was your date with Margaux

309
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:13,850
Things were fine...
Until... they weren't

310
00:18:15,780 --> 00:18:18,520
- Okay.What happened .
- I don't know

311
00:18:18,670 --> 00:18:20,310
She just-- She left
in the middle of it

312
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:24,870
What,for no reason.What's up,Jack

313
00:18:27,890 --> 00:18:30,950
I just... I blew it

314
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:35,540
I mean,I didn't want to,but
I just-- I couldn't handle it

315
00:18:38,630 --> 00:18:40,270
You know what this is,right

316
00:18:41,710 --> 00:18:47,390
- Yeah.
- I think... Maybe it's time to face it

317
00:18:53,910 --> 00:18:57,710
I must admit,I was a bit surprised
when I heard from your publicist

318
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:01,370
So she tells me you're
looking for some press coverage

319
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:04,370
Oh,uh,there must be some confusion

320
00:19:04,790 --> 00:19:07,960
What Ms Preston offered
you was an exclusive

321
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:09,750
Conrad Grayson is back

322
00:19:09,770 --> 00:19:14,320
He's a survivor... A
laudatory profile of sorts

323
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,730
It's out of the question

324
00:19:16,190 --> 00:19:18,260
We have to maintain
journalistic integrity

325
00:19:19,860 --> 00:19:22,580
And covering Daniel's wedding
isn't a conflict of interest

326
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:23,930
Touché,Mr Grayson

327
00:19:25,050 --> 00:19:27,840
But there is a difference
between a society piece

328
00:19:28,130 --> 00:19:29,860
and an advertisement for you

329
00:19:31,010 --> 00:19:36,880
Now,if you were to give me access
to all your papers and... archives...

330
00:19:37,230 --> 00:19:38,440
Then maybe we could talk

331
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:41,550
Ms Lemarchal,I'm not
here to dwell on the past

332
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:43,890
Well,if you're not willing
to be totally honest with me,

333
00:19:44,210 --> 00:19:45,980
I'm not comfortable moving forward

334
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:50,330
But I'm sure there's a
story in you no one expects

335
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,370
You just need the guts to tell it

336
00:19:57,610 --> 00:19:58,990
You see how easy this is

337
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:01,510
With you two on the same page,

338
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:05,520
it won't pull focus as we can
ease Conrad back into the spotlight

339
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:08,160
Well,this itinerary is too aggressive

340
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:12,980
Surely the 200 people I'm hosting
this evening means I've done my duty

341
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:16,430
You know better than most that
changing public opinion takes time

342
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:19,360
And I have mere weeks
until everyone sees you

343
00:20:19,570 --> 00:20:23,350
as the new ideal of a mother and
daughter-in-law - at the bridal shower

344
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:25,590
That should be an interesting challenge

345
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,250
Not for women of your stature

346
00:20:27,610 --> 00:20:32,080
If your conflict creates such sparks,
imagine what a partnership can do

347
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:33,860
Well,I'd certainly marvel to see it

348
00:20:34,490 --> 00:20:36,520
Aiden,what a coincidence

349
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:38,560
Well,in-- In
truth,it's not

350
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:43,100
I know I'm-- I'm being forward,
but I was hoping to steal Ms Thorne

351
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:44,870
I have nothing to say to you

352
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:47,950
Why don't you go,Emily

353
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:50,040
You clearly have things to resolve

354
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:55,790
Thank you for lunch,Bizzy

355
00:20:56,780 --> 00:20:59,140
- Of course.
- After you.Thank you

356
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,070
Sweet girl

357
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:06,250
Emily obviously craves your approval

358
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:09,730
You know,I would have assumed that
paying top dollar for a flat meant

359
00:21:09,930 --> 00:21:12,900
that Conrad got someone who
is better at reading people

360
00:21:14,390 --> 00:21:16,720
Yes.Well,on
second thought,I--

361
00:21:16,860 --> 00:21:20,560
Which is why I'm loathe to parade
around on a goodwill tour with her,

362
00:21:20,860 --> 00:21:23,570
not to mention her unresolved
feelings for Aiden Mathis

363
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:25,630
He's her ex,too

364
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:29,580
She is determined to make
me earn my keep,isn't she

365
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:30,910
"Too"

366
00:21:32,570 --> 00:21:35,270
Well,I probably shouldn't tell you this,

367
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,530
but young Emily was married once before

368
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:41,510
I beg your pardon

369
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,500
Don't worry. It was a mistake

370
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:44,980
I'm sure that's all there is to it

371
00:21:45,540 --> 00:21:47,230
One can never be too certain

372
00:21:47,930 --> 00:21:50,080
She was young.She was in love

373
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:51,690
Did she happen to mention a name

374
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:55,080
- Oh,I don't remember.
- Ronald... Roger

375
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:56,510
I'm sure I have it at the office

376
00:21:56,810 --> 00:21:59,200
Well,perhaps you can do
some investigating for me

377
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:00,890
And the takedown is all yours,Nolan

378
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:04,360
I'm sure the Graysons' 4th
of July party will serve

379
00:22:04,540 --> 00:22:06,120
as the perfect backdrop,don't you think

380
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:10,270
Well... Let the fireworks begin

381
00:22:24,290 --> 00:22:27,080
- Nice to see you.- Take
care.- Hey,Mom.- Quick photo

382
00:22:29,170 --> 00:22:33,670
Yeah.Okay. Well,Bizzy's certainly
making this an event to remember

383
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,950
She's documenting
every living inch of it

384
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:39,290
Well,I'm sure she'll be excluding Aiden,

385
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:42,680
seeing as he dragged your
fiancée out of lunch today

386
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,030
Emily told you,I'm sure

387
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:46,600
I think he's trying to
rekindle the relationship

388
00:22:47,030 --> 00:22:48,390
Do you have to read into everything

389
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:51,030
Just try and enjoy yourself

390
00:22:52,150 --> 00:22:53,120
- Hello,gentlemen.
- Hi

391
00:22:53,470 --> 00:22:56,040
The who's who of the
Hamptons is out in full force

392
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:58,050
I'd say we're a success

393
00:22:59,370 --> 00:23:02,980
Oh,and I have feelers out
for info on husband number one

394
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:05,580
Speaking of which,I
should probably find mine

395
00:23:07,270 --> 00:23:10,350
Why don't we keep our little fact
finding mission to ourselves,shall we

396
00:23:11,860 --> 00:23:15,040
Mother... You remember Sara

397
00:23:18,810 --> 00:23:19,960
Of course

398
00:23:20,780 --> 00:23:23,530
Oh,Ms Munello,I don't
mean to be indelicate,

399
00:23:23,710 --> 00:23:25,180
but wouldn't you be far more comfortable

400
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:27,330
watching the fireworks
in the field somewhere

401
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:30,540
Well,Charlotte was nice enough
to let me class it up tonight--

402
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:32,010
Pretend to be the one percent

403
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,280
Of what exactly,dear

404
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,140
Can I get you a refill

405
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:39,650
'Cause I could sure use a drink

406
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:47,180
Why on earth did you invite
that girl back into our house

407
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:52,020
Because I care about Daniel too
much to see him marry the wrong woman

408
00:23:52,820 --> 00:23:55,050
And I don't think Emily's
the one to make him happy

409
00:23:55,550 --> 00:23:57,950
You know I concur in
spades,but that doesn't explain

410
00:23:58,290 --> 00:24:00,510
the need to trot in
somebody off the rack

411
00:24:00,690 --> 00:24:01,710
Wake up,Mother

412
00:24:02,190 --> 00:24:05,770
I'm sure Daniel still has feelings for
Sara, and she still has feelings for him

413
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:08,030
They just need help remembering that

414
00:24:08,710 --> 00:24:12,640
So you think that Sara could be the
one who would put a stop to this wedding

415
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:16,730
Well,if you weren't so
focused on hating Emily

416
00:24:17,090 --> 00:24:20,180
and were more focused on worrying
about Daniel, you might see it,too

417
00:24:27,850 --> 00:24:34,130
So okay... proud of
me.I'd expect nothing less

418
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:43,560
Bizzy Preston... In the flesh

419
00:24:44,070 --> 00:24:46,770
Nols.It's been ages

420
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,850
Darling,you look marvelous

421
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:51,650
Likewise,and,uh,who's the arm candy

422
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:53,660
This is my husband Jeff

423
00:24:54,050 --> 00:24:55,150
Jeff,this is Nolan Ross

424
00:24:55,330 --> 00:24:56,970
of course.Pleasure to meet you,Nolan

425
00:24:57,190 --> 00:24:58,300
Oh,the pleasure is all mine

426
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:00,960
You dabble in PR as well?

427
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:03,660
Oh,no,no. I let my wife
stay in the spotlight

428
00:25:04,010 --> 00:25:04,860
She's good at it

429
00:25:05,620 --> 00:25:07,570
She is dedicated to her clients

430
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:12,700
You know,come to think of it,the
last time we crossed paths,

431
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:16,790
you were a bad girl,outing
me like that in the press

432
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:18,530
You mean that whole "Sage" thing

433
00:25:18,940 --> 00:25:20,190
You're welcome

434
00:25:20,650 --> 00:25:24,310
I took you out of the tech pages, and
I made you interesting to real people

435
00:25:24,570 --> 00:25:26,210
You did bring out my inner Armani

436
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:29,380
And besides,who could
stay mad at that face

437
00:25:29,620 --> 00:25:30,750
You just earned a cocktail

438
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:11,320
I wore this for one
night as a married man,

439
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,950
and I've worn it ever
since to honor you...

440
00:26:17,670 --> 00:26:19,740
Maybe subconsciously to convince people

441
00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:24,890
that I had someone to share
my days with,and... And nights

442
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:30,620
But I don't anymore

443
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:37,730
It's time for me to try to move on

444
00:26:49,660 --> 00:26:51,230
I miss you with all my heart

445
00:27:02,370 --> 00:27:04,740
I'm serious .The orange
jumpsuit washed me out

446
00:27:04,970 --> 00:27:07,360
So I said I preferred the
black and white stripes

447
00:27:07,570 --> 00:27:08,420
They wouldn't budge

448
00:27:08,510 --> 00:27:10,200
You are too much

449
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:11,390
You two seem to be having a good time

450
00:27:11,890 --> 00:27:14,960
Oh,Emily,you are so lucky to
have this one at arm's length

451
00:27:15,130 --> 00:27:17,060
God,the trouble you two must get into

452
00:27:17,270 --> 00:27:18,400
Nothing worth publicizing

453
00:27:19,300 --> 00:27:20,300
I was gonna ask you,

454
00:27:20,390 --> 00:27:22,220
what time is that museum
fund-raiser on Monday

455
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,590
Victoria would kill me if I'm late

456
00:27:23,730 --> 00:27:25,880
- As will I?
- Let me check

457
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,300
Where are my readers

458
00:27:28,650 --> 00:27:31,030
Oh,here,these, These are mine

459
00:27:31,710 --> 00:27:34,430
Oh,thank you,Nols.My little lifesaver

460
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:39,010
10:00

461
00:27:39,270 --> 00:27:42,290
And it is very important that you two put on
- a good show,my dear

462
00:27:42,490 --> 00:27:43,780
I will behave,I promise

463
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:46,200
- Enjoy the party .
- Thank you

464
00:27:46,860 --> 00:27:48,040
Now,where were we

465
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:51,400
Well,I was just about to
get,uh,another cocktail

466
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:52,580
What's your poison

467
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,200
Surprise me

468
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:59,410
- Okay.
- Oh,hi

469
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:17,000
Thank you,Nols,my little lifesaver

470
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:32,730
If it's a surprise you want,
I'm more than happy to oblige

471
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:50,280
You're looking dashing
this evening,Ms Thorne

472
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:53,070
As are you,MrMathis

473
00:28:53,910 --> 00:28:55,930
Well,I see you two have made peace

474
00:28:56,380 --> 00:29:01,240
We're trying,Victoria,seeing as you obviously
intend on having us both in your life

475
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:03,410
Oh,aren't you kind

476
00:29:03,630 --> 00:29:05,170
But don't do anything on my behalf

477
00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:10,800
Well,that wasn't part of the plan

478
00:29:11,030 --> 00:29:12,270
Victoria forced my hand

479
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:13,870
I had no choice but to be seen with you

480
00:29:14,130 --> 00:29:15,100
Mm,don't get used to it

481
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:19,240
Getting chummy with Aiden again

482
00:29:19,530 --> 00:29:21,090
Oh,we're just at the same party,Daniel

483
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,150
What did he have to say

484
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,240
Does it matter

485
00:29:23,430 --> 00:29:25,330
I'm just making the
best of a bad situation

486
00:29:25,950 --> 00:29:27,590
Don't tell me you're jealous

487
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:33,970
-No No,I'm not
- Good

488
00:29:34,430 --> 00:29:36,140
I was gonna go get some
food,if you want to join

489
00:29:36,660 --> 00:29:39,500
- In a minute I got a couple people I need to talk to.
-Okay

490
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:58,850
Word around the party is that
Conrad Grayson is writing his memoirs

491
00:29:59,050 --> 00:29:59,930
Is this true

492
00:30:00,550 --> 00:30:03,070
Indeed it is.Will you excuse us

493
00:30:03,620 --> 00:30:06,030
So you've decided to
discuss your past after all

494
00:30:07,110 --> 00:30:08,040
Well,you were right

495
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:09,450
The public deserves it

496
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:12,480
I plan to give it to them in my own way

497
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:15,770
Well,I would love to talk more about it

498
